{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1658,"text":"Imagine you are a part\nof a crew of astronauts"},{"time":6124,"text":"traveling to Mars or some distant planet."},{"time":9854,"text":"The travel time could take a year"},{"time":12910,"text":"or even longer."},{"time":14836,"text":"The space on board and the resources"},{"time":17797,"text":"would be limited."},{"time":19361,"text":"So you and the crew would have\nto figure out how to produce food"},{"time":23972,"text":"with minimal inputs."},{"time":26169,"text":"What if you could bring with you\njust a few packets of seeds,"},{"time":30965,"text":"and grow crops in a matter of hours?"},{"time":34914,"text":"And what if those crops\nwould then make more seeds,"},{"time":38375,"text":"enabling you to feed the entire crew"},{"time":41453,"text":"with just those few packets of seeds\nfor the duration of the trip?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46465,"text":"Well, the scientists at NASA actually\nfigured out a way to do this."},{"time":51546,"text":"What they came up with\nwas actually quite interesting."},{"time":54213,"text":"It involved microorganisms,"},{"time":56133,"text":"which are single-celled organisms."},{"time":58732,"text":"And they also used hydrogen from water."},{"time":61511,"text":"The types of microbes that they used\nwere called hydrogenotrophs,"},{"time":65623,"text":"and with these hydrogenotrophs,\nyou can create a virtuous carbon cycle"},{"time":70937,"text":"that would sustain life\nonboard a spacecraft."},{"time":74525,"text":"Astronauts would breathe out\ncarbon dioxide,"},{"time":78241,"text":"that carbon dioxide would then\nbe captured by the microbes"},{"time":82066,"text":"and converted into a nutritious,\ncarbon-rich crop."},{"time":86287,"text":"The astronauts would then eat\nthat carbon-rich crop"},{"time":89902,"text":"and exhale the carbon out\nin the form of carbon dioxide,"},{"time":93916,"text":"which would then be captured\nby the microbes,"},{"time":96164,"text":"to create a nutritious crop,"},{"time":97823,"text":"which then would be exhaled\nin the form of carbon dioxide"},{"time":100742,"text":"by the astronauts."},{"time":102176,"text":"So in this way, a closed-loop\ncarbon cycle is created."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105821,"text":"So why is this important?"},{"time":108158,"text":"We need carbon to survive as humans,"},{"time":110872,"text":"and we get our carbon from food."},{"time":113237,"text":"On a long space journey,"},{"time":114944,"text":"you simply wouldn't be able to pick up\nany carbon along the way,"},{"time":118287,"text":"so you'd have to figure out\nhow to recycle it on board."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121817,"text":"This is a clever solution, right?"},{"time":124825,"text":"But the thing is, that research\ndidn't really go anywhere."},{"time":128553,"text":"We haven't yet gone to Mars.\nWe haven't yet gone to another planet."},{"time":132299,"text":"And this was actually done\nin the '60s and '70s."},{"time":135365,"text":"So a colleague of mine,\nDr. John Reed, and I,"},{"time":138746,"text":"were interested, actually,\nin carbon recycling here on Earth."},{"time":142741,"text":"We wanted to come up\nwith technical solutions"},{"time":144996,"text":"to address climate change."},{"time":146780,"text":"And we discovered this research"},{"time":149025,"text":"by reading some papers published\nin the '60s -- 1967 and later --"},{"time":153469,"text":"articles about this work."},{"time":156292,"text":"And we thought it was a really good idea."},{"time":158774,"text":"So we said, well, Earth\nis actually like a spaceship."},{"time":162370,"text":"We have limited space\nand limited resources,"},{"time":165806,"text":"and on Earth, we really do\nneed to figure out"},{"time":168013,"text":"how to recycle our carbon better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171202,"text":"So we had the idea,"},{"time":173373,"text":"can we take some of these\nNASA-type ideas and apply them"},{"time":180147,"text":"to our carbon problem here on Earth?"},{"time":182936,"text":"Could we cultivate\nthese NASA-type microbes"},{"time":185592,"text":"in order to make\nvaluable products here on Earth?"},{"time":189241,"text":"We started a company to do it."},{"time":191717,"text":"And in that company, we discovered\nthat these hydrogenotrophs --"},{"time":196421,"text":"which I'll actually call\nnature's supercharged carbon recyclers --"},{"time":200382,"text":"we found that they are a powerful\nclass of microbes"},{"time":203225,"text":"that had been largely overlooked\nand understudied,"},{"time":207077,"text":"and that they could make\nsome really valuable products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210544,"text":"So we began cultivating these products,\nthese microbes, in our lab."},{"time":215115,"text":"We found that we can make\nessential amino acids from carbon dioxide"},{"time":218994,"text":"using these microbes."},{"time":220483,"text":"And we even made a protein-rich meal"},{"time":223552,"text":"that has an amino acid profile\nsimilar to what you might find"},{"time":228047,"text":"in some animal proteins."},{"time":230523,"text":"We began cultivating them even further,"},{"time":232957,"text":"and we found that we can make oil."},{"time":234898,"text":"Oils are used to manufacture\nmany products."},{"time":237738,"text":"We made an oil that was similar\nto a citrus oil,"},{"time":241095,"text":"which can be used for flavoring\nand for fragrances,"},{"time":244204,"text":"but it also can be used\nas a biodegradable cleaner"},{"time":246855,"text":"or even as a jet fuel."},{"time":249236,"text":"And we made an oil\nthat's similar to palm oil."},{"time":252065,"text":"Palm oil is used to manufacture"},{"time":254049,"text":"a wide range of consumer\nand industrial goods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258873,"text":"We began working with manufacturers\nto scale up this technology,"},{"time":263639,"text":"and we're currently working with them"},{"time":265470,"text":"to bring some of these products to market."},{"time":268756,"text":"We believe this type of technology\ncan indeed help us"},{"time":271720,"text":"profitably recycle carbon dioxide\ninto valuable products --"},{"time":275777,"text":"something that's beneficial\nfor the planet"},{"time":277839,"text":"but also beneficial for business."},{"time":280383,"text":"That's what we're doing today."},{"time":282225,"text":"But tomorrow, this type of technology\nand using these types of microbes"},{"time":286479,"text":"actually could help us\ndo something even greater"},{"time":289266,"text":"if we take it to the next level."},{"time":292045,"text":"We believe that this type of technology"},{"time":294487,"text":"can actually help us address\nan issue with agriculture"},{"time":297750,"text":"and allow us to create\na type of agriculture that's sustainable,"},{"time":302299,"text":"that will allow us to scale\nto meet the demands of tomorrow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306585,"text":"And why might we need\na sustainable agriculture?"},{"time":310325,"text":"Well, actually, it is estimated"},{"time":312537,"text":"that the population will reach\nabout 10 billion by 2050,"},{"time":317798,"text":"and we're projecting that we will need\nto increase food production"},{"time":321003,"text":"by 70 percent."},{"time":323182,"text":"In addition, we will need many more\nresources and raw materials"},{"time":326444,"text":"to make consumer goods\nand industrial goods."},{"time":329571,"text":"So how will we scale to meet that demand?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":332669,"text":"Well, modern agriculture simply cannot\nsustainably scale to meet that demand."},{"time":338760,"text":"There are a number of reasons why."},{"time":341309,"text":"One of them is that modern agriculture\nis one of the largest emitters"},{"time":346169,"text":"of greenhouse gases."},{"time":347774,"text":"In fact, it emits more greenhouse gases"},{"time":351421,"text":"than our cars, our trucks, our planes"},{"time":354549,"text":"and our trains combined."},{"time":357009,"text":"Another reason is that modern ag\nsimply takes up a whole lot of land."},{"time":362549,"text":"We have cleared 19.4 million square miles\nfor crops and livestock."},{"time":369446,"text":"What does that look like?"},{"time":371118,"text":"Well, that's roughly the size\nof South America and Africa combined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377041,"text":"Let me give you a specific example."},{"time":379324,"text":"In Indonesia, an amount\nof virgin rainforest was cleared"},{"time":384304,"text":"totaling the size\nof approximately Ireland,"},{"time":387710,"text":"between 2000 and 2012."},{"time":390717,"text":"Just think of all\nof the species, the diversity,"},{"time":393947,"text":"that was removed in the process,"},{"time":395861,"text":"whether plant life, insects\nor animal life."},{"time":399145,"text":"And a natural carbon sink\nwas also removed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402437,"text":"So let me make this real for you."},{"time":404896,"text":"This clearing happened primarily\nto make room for palm plantations."},{"time":409399,"text":"And as I mentioned before,"},{"time":410798,"text":"palm oil is used\nto manufacture many products."},{"time":414371,"text":"In fact, it is estimated\nthat over 50 percent of consumer products"},{"time":418322,"text":"are manufactured using palm oil."},{"time":421671,"text":"And that includes things\nlike ice cream, cookies ..."},{"time":425506,"text":"It includes cooking oils."},{"time":427397,"text":"It also includes detergents,\nlotions, soaps."},{"time":431594,"text":"You and I both\nprobably have numerous items"},{"time":436395,"text":"in our kitchens and our bathrooms"},{"time":438920,"text":"that were manufactured using palm oil."},{"time":441450,"text":"So you and I are direct beneficiaries\nof removed rainforests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447691,"text":"Modern ag has some problems,"},{"time":449804,"text":"and we need solutions\nif we want to scale sustainably."},{"time":455151,"text":"I believe that microbes\ncan be a part of the answer --"},{"time":459701,"text":"specifically, these supercharged\ncarbon recyclers."},{"time":463708,"text":"These supercharged carbon recyclers,"},{"time":466254,"text":"like plants, serve as\nthe natural recyclers"},{"time":470309,"text":"in their ecosystems where they thrive."},{"time":472454,"text":"And they thrive in exotic places on Earth,"},{"time":474674,"text":"like hydrothermal vents and hot springs."},{"time":477543,"text":"In those ecosystems,\nthey take carbon and recycle it"},{"time":480830,"text":"into the nutrients needed\nfor those ecosystems."},{"time":483916,"text":"And they're rich in nutrients,"},{"time":485399,"text":"such as oils and proteins,\nminerals and carbohydrates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492025,"text":"And actually, microbes are already\nan integral part of our everyday lives."},{"time":497335,"text":"If you enjoy a glass of pinot noir\non a Friday night,"},{"time":501566,"text":"after a long, hard work week,"},{"time":503534,"text":"then you are enjoying\na product of microbes."},{"time":507176,"text":"If you enjoy a beer\nfrom your local microbrewery --"},{"time":509882,"text":"a product of microbes."},{"time":511526,"text":"Or bread, or cheese, or yogurt."},{"time":515060,"text":"These are all products of microbes."},{"time":517729,"text":"But the beauty and power associated\nwith these supercharged carbon recyclers"},{"time":523038,"text":"lies in the fact that they can\nactually produce in a matter of hours"},{"time":528162,"text":"versus months."},{"time":529512,"text":"That means we can make crops"},{"time":531479,"text":"much faster than we're making them today."},{"time":535685,"text":"They grow in the dark,"},{"time":537344,"text":"so they can grow in any season"},{"time":539915,"text":"and in any geography and any location."},{"time":543159,"text":"They can grow in containers\nthat require minimal space."},{"time":547562,"text":"And we can get to a type\nof vertical agriculture."},{"time":551540,"text":"Instead of our traditional\nhorizontal agriculture"},{"time":554221,"text":"that requires so much land,"},{"time":555974,"text":"we can scale vertically,"},{"time":557571,"text":"and as a result\nproduce much more product per area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564187,"text":"If we implement this type of approach\nand use these carbon recyclers,"},{"time":568675,"text":"then we wouldn't have to remove\nany more rainforests"},{"time":571995,"text":"to make the food and the goods\nthat we consume."},{"time":576524,"text":"Because, at a large scale,"},{"time":578761,"text":"you can actually make 10,000 times\nmore output per land area"},{"time":584093,"text":"than you could -- for instance,\nif you used soybeans --"},{"time":587272,"text":"if you planted soybeans\non that same area of land"},{"time":590356,"text":"over a period of a year."},{"time":592531,"text":"Ten thousand times\nover a period of a year."},{"time":596300,"text":"So this is what I mean\nby a new type of agriculture."},{"time":600613,"text":"And this is what I mean\nby developing a system"},{"time":603945,"text":"that allows us to sustainably scale\nto meet the demands of 10 billion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610704,"text":"And what would be the products\nof this new type of agriculture?"},{"time":614323,"text":"Well, we've already made a protein meal,"},{"time":616530,"text":"so you can imagine something\nsimilar to a soybean meal,"},{"time":619817,"text":"or even cornmeal, or wheat flour."},{"time":622203,"text":"We've already made oils,"},{"time":623580,"text":"so you can imagine something\nsimilar to coconut oil"},{"time":627282,"text":"or olive oil or soybean oil."},{"time":630042,"text":"So this type of crop can\nactually produce the nutrients"},{"time":634304,"text":"that would give us pasta and bread,"},{"time":636623,"text":"cakes, nutritional items of many sorts."},{"time":640226,"text":"Furthermore, since oil is used\nto manufacture multiple other goods,"},{"time":647162,"text":"industrial products and consumer products,"},{"time":649242,"text":"you can imagine being able to make\ndetergents, soaps, lotions, etc.,"},{"time":654069,"text":"using these types of crops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657382,"text":"Not only are we running out of space,"},{"time":660286,"text":"but if we continue to operate\nunder the status quo"},{"time":663478,"text":"with modern agriculture,"},{"time":664975,"text":"we run the risk of robbing our progeny\nof a beautiful planet."},{"time":670216,"text":"But it doesn't have to be this way."},{"time":672627,"text":"We can imagine a future of abundance."},{"time":676154,"text":"Let us create systems that keep\nplanet Earth, our spaceship,"},{"time":682054,"text":"not only from not crashing,"},{"time":684410,"text":"but let us also develop systems\nand ways of living"},{"time":688564,"text":"that will be beneficial\nto the lives of ourselves"},{"time":692746,"text":"and the 10 billion that will\nbe on this planet by 2050."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696817,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698056,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}